Mom?

5
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,628
Come on, guys, push it!

6
00:03:44,022 --> 00:03:46,962
Move when you got the ball!
Nobody's moving there.

7
00:03:47,318 --> 00:03:49,966
Know where your teammates are!

8
00:03:51,034 --> 00:03:52,932
All right, hold up. Hold it up.

9
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:57,029
New ball.
We are going to play with this ball.

10
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,141
Invisiball.

11
00:04:02,616 --> 00:04:04,768
It's funny. You think it's silly.

12
00:04:04,769 --> 00:04:06,797
Practice is the place
it's okay to feel silly.

13
00:04:06,798 --> 00:04:07,986
The practice floor.

14
00:04:07,986 --> 00:04:10,517
Not with people watching you play.

15
00:04:10,518 --> 00:04:12,736
Alright, you guys.
Run a couple plays.

16
00:04:12,737 --> 00:04:13,842
Set it up. Three game.

17
00:04:13,843 --> 00:04:15,350
Where's the ball?

18
00:04:15,384 --> 00:04:17,644
- In my mind, coach.
- It is in your mind.

19
00:04:17,645 --> 00:04:21,148
One brain! There you go!
That's the way to move it!

20
00:04:21,149 --> 00:04:23,814
You play better with the
invisiball than the real ball.

21
00:04:32,371 --> 00:04:34,174
-Hey, kiddo.
-Hey, how are you?

22
00:04:34,175 --> 00:04:35,182
Good, how are you?

23
00:04:35,183 --> 00:04:38,881
You spaz.
Yeah, I was there all alone.

24
00:04:38,882 --> 00:04:39,895
-Hi.
-Hey.

25
00:04:41,692 --> 00:04:43,260
You're late.

26
00:04:44,387 --> 00:04:45,476
Practice ran long.

27
00:04:46,999 --> 00:04:50,232
Oh, uh, Clyde, shoes, please?

28
00:04:57,892 --> 00:04:59,521
What is this?

29
00:04:59,522 --> 00:05:02,604
I needed work space for the business.
We're up and running.

30
00:05:02,605 --> 00:05:04,542
Hmm.

31
00:05:05,395 --> 00:05:06,879
Yeah.

32
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:10,894
The jewelry design. I told
you I was getting back into it.

33
00:05:15,138 --> 00:05:17,010
Stephanie, I had a bunch of stuff in here.

34
00:05:17,011 --> 00:05:19,838
I boxed up your stuff.
Your name's on it.

35
00:05:19,839 --> 00:05:21,775
Everything's in the closet.

36
00:05:21,775 --> 00:05:26,256
Don't you think I should
have packed up my office?

37
00:05:26,257 --> 00:05:28,354
It's not your office anymore.

38
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,582
Hey, kiddo. You ready to go?

39
00:05:46,231 --> 00:05:47,891
Which one you think is a better slogan?

40
00:05:47,892 --> 00:05:50,114
"Stop The Killing, Eat Vegetables...

41
00:05:50,115 --> 00:05:52,168
...or When You Eat Animals,
You Become One?

42
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,897
First of all, that is awesome...

43
00:05:55,898 --> 00:05:59,300
...but Stop The Killing
is super catchy.

44
00:05:59,301 --> 00:06:01,923
-Get my message?
-Loud and clear.

45
00:06:01,924 --> 00:06:05,266
Miss Shandy said that if we get
200 signatures on our petition...

46
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:06,644
...she will
take it to the principal...

47
00:06:06,645 --> 00:06:09,457
...and they'll consider
meat-free Mondays.

48
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:11,981
Wow, that will make you so popular.

49
00:06:11,982 --> 00:06:15,921
Dad, were all one big
family on this planet...

50
00:06:15,922 --> 00:06:17,051
...no matter what species...

51
00:06:17,052 --> 00:06:19,178
...and we don't eat family, do we?

52
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:20,791
No, we certainly do not.

53
00:06:23,124 --> 00:06:24,420
-Hi, Clyde.
-Hey.

54
00:06:24,421 --> 00:06:28,080
Careful. You are entering
a shoe-free zone.

55
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,652
I know. I got that
sign for Stephanie.

56
00:06:30,653 --> 00:06:33,887
You wouldn't believe
what's dragged indoors.

57
00:06:33,888 --> 00:06:34,849
I'm sure I wouldn't.

58
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:36,891
-Hey!
-Hi.

59
00:06:36,892 --> 00:06:38,426
What are you up to tonight?

60
00:06:38,427 --> 00:06:40,962
-Going to a concert.
-Nice.

61
00:06:40,963 --> 00:06:42,946
Season tickets. Wagner.

62
00:06:42,947 --> 00:06:47,144
Wagner? Stephanie loves Wagner,
don't you, dear?

63
00:06:47,145 --> 00:06:49,940
I'll have them back Sunday after lunch.

64
00:06:49,941 --> 00:06:50,798
Okay.

65
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:57,017
Em's still vegetarian, so keep an eye
on her, and her allergies, please.

66
00:06:57,018 --> 00:06:58,577
Last time she got hives.

67
00:06:58,578 --> 00:07:01,660
And healthy food,
stuff that grows on trees.

68
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:04,185
No pizza, please. I mean it.

69
00:07:04,186 --> 00:07:04,957
You done?

70
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:06,335
Yes.

71
00:07:06,336 --> 00:07:08,438
-Stephanie...
-Yes?

72
00:07:08,439 --> 00:07:10,404
I think I got this.

73
00:07:10,405 --> 00:07:11,657
-Okay.
-Okay.

74
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:17,553
-Bye, you guys! I love you!
-Bye!

75
00:07:20,504 --> 00:07:25,002
-Brett says I have an overbite.
-Give me a break, your teeth are fine.

76
00:07:25,003 --> 00:07:28,521
Brett's job is to tell
people they have bad teeth.

77
00:07:28,522 --> 00:07:29,581
That's how he makes money.

78
00:07:29,582 --> 00:07:32,043
He said he'd fix it for free.

79
00:07:32,044 --> 00:07:34,263
Uh, Dad?

80
00:07:34,264 --> 00:07:35,801
Yeah?

81
00:07:35,802 --> 00:07:38,109
You passed your apartment.

82
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:40,172
Oh, I did, didn't I?

83
00:07:40,173 --> 00:07:41,337
Ta-dah!

84
00:07:41,338 --> 00:07:42,492
What is it?

85
00:07:42,492 --> 00:07:45,045
What is it? This is our new house.

86
00:07:45,046 --> 00:07:47,633
-It's in the middle of nowhere.
-Isn't it awesome?

87
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:49,911
And critters come by from the woods.

88
00:07:49,912 --> 00:07:52,363
Yesterday, two raccoons on our porch.

89
00:07:52,364 --> 00:07:53,172
Really?

90
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:55,615
Come on, Mopey McGee.

91
00:07:56,568 --> 00:08:00,922
Wow, this is pretty cool.

92
00:08:00,923 --> 00:08:03,336
Right? Bedrooms are upstairs.

93
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,613
I call the room facing the woods!

94
00:08:13,614 --> 00:08:15,798
You got it. That's your room.

95
00:08:15,799 --> 00:08:17,800
Dad, there's a doggie door!

96
00:08:19,526 --> 00:08:22,059
Lets get a dog from
the shelter. Please.

97
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:24,918
Please, please, please, please.

98
00:08:24,918 --> 00:08:27,720
You've got to be kidding me.
This does not work on me anymore.

99
00:08:27,721 --> 00:08:30,472
Daddy, yes, it does. Please.

100
00:08:33,582 --> 00:08:34,555
Cheers.

101
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:36,653
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

102
00:08:39,524 --> 00:08:41,455
I think Mom would
really like this house.

103
00:08:41,456 --> 00:08:42,874
We should invite her for breakfast.

104
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:47,737
Mom and Dad officially
divorced three months ago.

105
00:08:47,738 --> 00:08:49,596
Mom's not coming for pancakes.

106
00:08:49,597 --> 00:08:51,618
-That's enough.
-Its getting old.

107
00:08:51,619 --> 00:08:54,394
She thinks you're
getting back together.

108
00:08:54,395 --> 00:08:59,571
Em, your mom and I,
we just sort of, uh...

109
00:08:59,572 --> 00:09:02,463
...we forgot how to get along.

110
00:09:02,464 --> 00:09:05,684
And you both are moving on with your lives.

111
00:09:05,685 --> 00:09:09,137
I know. That's what Mom always says.

112
00:09:10,034 --> 00:09:11,888
Your mom says that?

113
00:09:14,363 --> 00:09:18,195
Okay. Then, there you have it.
You know, its for the best.

114
00:09:18,196 --> 00:09:22,786
Okay? So let's have our dinner.

115
00:09:22,787 --> 00:09:24,878
I'm not hungry anymore.

116
00:09:26,544 --> 00:09:28,130
Alright, clear your plate.

117
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,265
Hannah...

118
00:09:37,266 --> 00:09:40,508
You can't say that. It upsets your sister.

119
00:09:41,524 --> 00:09:45,775
For real?
You're going to blame this on me?

120
00:09:45,776 --> 00:09:48,369
Nice, Dad.

121
00:09:52,737 --> 00:09:56,657
"Walk a little faster,"
said the whiting to the snail.

122
00:09:56,658 --> 00:10:01,004
"There's a porpoise close behind us,
and he's treading on my tail."

123
00:10:01,004 --> 00:10:02,543
How was your day today?

124
00:10:02,544 --> 00:10:05,384
Okay. How was yours?

125
00:10:05,385 --> 00:10:06,816
Dinner was a failure.

126
00:10:06,817 --> 00:10:09,848
Make sure Mom doesn't
find out about dinner.

127
00:10:09,849 --> 00:10:12,771
She'll be mad pizza
doesn't grow on trees.

128
00:10:12,772 --> 00:10:15,202
I'll give you $5 if
you don't tell your momther.

129
00:10:15,203 --> 00:10:18,235
Make it 35 and we have a deal.

130
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,292
Go to sleep.

131
00:10:24,599 --> 00:10:25,841
Leave the door open.

132
00:10:25,842 --> 00:10:28,132
What's the matter? You scared?

133
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:31,937
No. Just... I want it open, okay?

134
00:10:42,455 --> 00:10:44,828
Dad, you need dishes.

135
00:10:46,141 --> 00:10:47,635
Okay.

136
00:10:47,636 --> 00:10:50,241
<i>Hey, Clyde, its Trevor down at NC.</i>

137
00:10:50,242 --> 00:10:52,890
<i>Call me. I want to talk to you.</i>

138
00:10:52,891 --> 00:10:54,039
<i>Hope you're good, pal.</i>

139
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,377
Dad, look! I'm a lady.

140
00:11:20,316 --> 00:11:21,836
Cool.

141
00:11:37,445 --> 00:11:39,848
-Daddy, can I get this?
-That is a lovely hat.

142
00:11:39,849 --> 00:11:42,028
Whatever you want, kiddo.

143
00:11:42,029 --> 00:11:44,934
So we found a couple things.
What's the damage?

144
00:11:46,165 --> 00:11:49,339
-How about 55?
-55.

145
00:11:52,392 --> 00:11:55,238
My daughters cleaned me out.
I have $48.

146
00:11:55,239 --> 00:11:56,815
-We'll put something back.
-Oh, no.

147
00:11:56,816 --> 00:11:58,814
-You sure?
-Yeah.

148
00:11:58,815 --> 00:12:00,359
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

149
00:12:01,891 --> 00:12:05,017
You're clearing out.
You moving or something?

150
00:12:05,018 --> 00:12:08,642
-No. Some of bills came up.
-Oh.

151
00:12:41,615 --> 00:12:48,036
No! No!

152
00:12:59,354 --> 00:13:03,671
Look at these carvings.
They're so pretty.

153
00:13:05,462 --> 00:13:07,586
These directions are ridiculous.

154
00:13:07,587 --> 00:13:11,378
Em, do me a favor and hand
me the screwdriver, please?

155
00:13:12,266 --> 00:13:14,854
But Daddy,
you said you'd get this open.

156
00:13:17,462 --> 00:13:19,595
Well, that's weird.
There aren't any seams.

157
00:13:20,451 --> 00:13:21,910
What does that mean?

158
00:13:21,911 --> 00:13:26,361
It means whoever made this
didn't want anybody to open it...

159
00:13:26,362 --> 00:13:29,359
...or they didn't want
anybody to open it easily.

160
00:13:31,103 --> 00:13:34,662
You hear that?
There's something in there.

161
00:13:34,663 --> 00:13:39,351
So somebody had to open it,
once upon a time.

162
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:41,619
That is absolutely correct.

163
00:13:44,037 --> 00:13:46,815
-Daddy, no.
-I have to take it.

164
00:13:46,816 --> 00:13:49,734
-Trevor. Sorry, I missed your calls.
-Daddy.

165
00:13:49,735 --> 00:13:50,630
<i>How's my old friend doing?</i>

166
00:13:50,631 --> 00:13:51,591
Good.

167
00:13:51,307 --> 00:13:52,318
Daddy--

168
00:13:52,319 --> 00:13:54,230
<i>You run a good program up there.</i>

169
00:13:54,231 --> 00:13:56,307
<i>You have two conference titles.</i>

170
00:13:56,308 --> 00:13:58,194
You calling just to chat?

171
00:13:58,195 --> 00:14:00,017
<i>Our board is taking note.</i>

172
00:14:00,018 --> 00:14:04,158
<i>Thought it was time you come to
North Carolina, discuss your future.</i>

173
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:06,085
What are we talking about here?

174
00:14:06,086 --> 00:14:09,406
<i>Talking about you moving
up to Division One.</i>

175
00:14:09,407 --> 00:14:10,962
Does Coach Hill know you doing this?

176
00:14:10,963 --> 00:14:12,128
<i>He's retiring.</i>

177
00:14:12,129 --> 00:14:14,443
<i>He told me to contact you.</i>

178
00:14:14,444 --> 00:14:18,375
<i>Said the school needs one
of their own to come take the reins.</i>

179
00:14:18,376 --> 00:14:22,205
What can I say?
Hell, yes, I'm interested.

180
00:16:37,581 --> 00:16:40,032
-What's going on?
-I don't know. It wasn't me.

181
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:44,049
-Dad!
-Hannah! What is it?

182
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,468
It was on my face! Get it off!

183
00:16:45,468 --> 00:16:48,061
-What are you talking about?
-It's under the covers!

184
00:16:53,007 --> 00:16:55,082
Dad!

185
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:58,273
-You did that on my bed.
-You told me to kill it.

186
00:16:58,274 --> 00:17:00,240
I told you to get it out.

187
00:17:00,241 --> 00:17:02,206
God, Dad.

188
00:17:04,486 --> 00:17:06,294
She told me to kill it.

189
00:17:09,865 --> 00:17:11,552
It's a moth!

190
00:17:19,573 --> 00:17:23,508
Make some noise for the
most dazzling divas of dance...

191
00:17:23,509 --> 00:17:25,798
...who always bring it fierce...

192
00:17:25,799 --> 00:17:28,611
...the Silverstars!

193
00:17:28,612 --> 00:17:29,573
Make me a home,
on my own, betta make that bedrock

194
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:38,338
Hey, are you okay?

195
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:41,495
-I feel funny.
-What?

196
00:17:41,496 --> 00:17:44,363
-I feel funny.
-What do you mean?

197
00:17:47,119 --> 00:17:48,871
I don't feel like me.

198
00:17:48,872 --> 00:17:51,736
I know this stuff
with Mom and Dad sucks...

199
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:55,575
...but we're just the kids,
and they're the adults...

200
00:17:55,576 --> 00:17:58,716
...and we have to go
along with their mistakes.

201
00:17:58,717 --> 00:18:02,757
But you'll feel better if
you just stopped giving a shit.

202
00:18:15,586 --> 00:18:19,616
Hi! Hey! Oh...

203
00:18:19,617 --> 00:18:20,868
Oh, hi, Mommy.

204
00:18:20,869 --> 00:18:22,834
-I missed you guys.
-I missed you too.

205
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,008
How was the weekend?

206
00:18:24,009 --> 00:18:26,826
It was good. We had pizza.

207
00:18:26,827 --> 00:18:30,178
Wow, yes,
the new house has a pizza tree.

208
00:18:30,179 --> 00:18:32,854
-Is Jen's mom coming?
-Oh, yeah.

209
00:18:32,855 --> 00:18:35,053
Your outfit is on your bed...

210
00:18:35,054 --> 00:18:37,660
...and take one of your
allergy pills just in case.

211
00:18:37,661 --> 00:18:40,594
If one of your players had food allergies...

212
00:18:40,595 --> 00:18:44,358
...you'd write the cafeteria
ladies with menu demands.

213
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,454
Cut me some slack.

214
00:18:49,082 --> 00:18:50,214
I was going get the boxes.

215
00:18:50,215 --> 00:18:52,450
-Okay.
-Okay.

216
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,441
What's with this guy?
Is he moving in or what?

217
00:19:01,442 --> 00:19:05,040
No. No, we're just dating.

218
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:06,168
You're just dating?

219
00:19:06,169 --> 00:19:09,474
He's awfully comfortable
in the kitchen.

220
00:19:09,475 --> 00:19:10,815
Back off, Clyde.

221
00:19:10,815 --> 00:19:14,496
-In his antiseptic socks.
-At least he's present.

222
00:19:14,497 --> 00:19:15,798
Excuse me?

223
00:19:15,799 --> 00:19:17,400
Presence, attendance...

224
00:19:17,401 --> 00:19:19,308
...being in the moment
as opposed to absent.

225
00:19:19,309 --> 00:19:21,568
-Like you.
-I know what it means.

226
00:19:21,569 --> 00:19:23,961
-Don't forget your stuff.
-Fine.

227
00:20:01,053 --> 00:20:02,118
Hello?

228
00:20:02,119 --> 00:20:04,163
<i>Clyde, it's Trevor.</i>

229
00:20:04,163 --> 00:20:04,799
Hey.

230
00:20:04,799 --> 00:20:05,886
<i>Got your flight lined up.</i>

231
00:20:05,887 --> 00:20:09,358
<i>I'll have the university
pick you up when you land.</i>

232
00:20:09,359 --> 00:20:11,204
<i>-Quite the welcome.
-You'll love it.</i>

233
00:20:11,205 --> 00:20:14,190
<i>Okay. Thank you for calling.</i>

234
00:20:14,191 --> 00:20:15,629
<i>Keep me informed. Alright, bye.</i>

235
00:20:15,630 --> 00:20:17,165
So she's in the middle row.

236
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:20,334
-Hannah's dance is next week.
-Oh!

237
00:20:20,335 --> 00:20:22,723
It's her first time with a real audience.

238
00:20:22,723 --> 00:20:24,848
-That's cool.
-Are you gonna make it?

239
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:26,412
Heck, yes, I'm coming.

240
00:20:26,413 --> 00:20:29,175
Mom will be there,
so don't feel obligated.

241
00:20:29,176 --> 00:20:32,085
Are you kidding?
I'll be in the front row.

242
00:20:34,050 --> 00:20:35,817
What's in your mouth?

243
00:20:35,818 --> 00:20:36,777
Hannah, I told you,
your teeth were perfect.

244
00:20:36,778 --> 00:20:41,626
No, you said it was my decision,
and I don't want to be disfigured.

245
00:20:41,627 --> 00:20:44,234
Disfigured?
Who said you were disfigured?

246
00:20:44,234 --> 00:20:46,934
I did. I'm totally disfigured.

247
00:20:46,935 --> 00:20:48,912
You are perfect.

248
00:21:03,479 --> 00:21:04,725
Dad?

249
00:21:04,725 --> 00:21:05,774
What? What's wrong?

250
00:21:07,229 --> 00:21:08,173
Go back outside.

251
00:21:08,173 --> 00:21:09,879
-Is someone in the house?
-Go

252
00:21:26,328 --> 00:21:27,799
